results.deck: Hi Tech Expressions was an American console game company that existed during the early 1990s. During the course of its existence, the company made primarily juvenile-oriented games for young boys and girls. While it made a few adolescent-oriented games like Hunt for Red October and War in Middle Earth (derived from the classic book The Lord of the Rings by J. R. R. Tolkien), it could not shake its reputation for making games marketed towards children. The company was bought and sold by NewKidCo (Which merge
